data.text:
The marriage of Prince George, later Duke of Kent & Princess Marina of Greece and Denmark in Westminster Abbey, London, UK, Nov 29th 1934. Their wedding was the first royal wedding ceremony to be broadcast by wireless and using microphones and loud speakers. Her dress was designed by designed by Edward Molyneux. Their 1st home was at 3 Belgrave Square. The Princess was widowed in 1942, when her husband was killed in a plane crash on active service. During WW II, Marina trained as a nurse for three months under the pseudonym "Sister Kay".
